  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best movies of the last two decades?",
  "response": "Determining the best movies of the last two decades can be subjective and can vary based on different criteria such as critical acclaim, audience reception, and awards. However, here are some of the most highly regarded and influential films from 2003 to 2023:\n\n1. **The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King (2003)** - Directed by Peter Jackson, this epic fantasy film concluded the Lord of the Rings trilogy and won 11 Academy Awards.\n \n2. **The Dark Knight (2008)** - Directed by Christopher Nolan, this superhero film redefined the genre and featured a legendary performance by Heath Ledger as the Joker.\n\n3. **Avatar (2009)** - Directed by James Cameron, this groundbreaking science fiction film pushed the boundaries of visual effects and became one of the highest-grossing films of all time.\n\n4. **Inception (2010)** - Another masterpiece by Christopher Nolan, this sci-fi thriller captivated audiences with its complex narrative and innovative concepts.\n\n5. **The Social Network (2010)** - Directed by David Fincher, this biographical drama about the founding of Facebook received critical acclaim for its screenplay and performances.\n\n6. **Boyhood (2014)** - Directed by Richard Linklater, this coming-of-age drama was filmed over 12 years and received praise for its unique production and storytelling.\n\n7. **Mad Max: Fury Road (2015)** - Directed by George Miller, this post-apocalyptic action film was lauded for its stunning visuals, intense action, and innovative design.\n\n8. **La La Land (2016)** - Directed by Damien Chazelle, this musical romantic comedy-drama won several Oscars and captivated audiences with its performances and musical numbers.\n\n9. **Moonlight (2016)** - Directed by Barry Jenkins, this coming-of-age drama won the Academy Award for Best Picture and was praised for its poignant storytelling and performances.\n\n10. **Parasite (2019)** - Directed by Bong Joon-ho, this South Korean dark comedy thriller received international acclaim and won the Academy Award for Best Picture, making history as the first non-English language film to do so.\n\n11. **Joker (2019)** - Directed by Todd Phillips, this psychological thriller featured Joaquin Phoenix\u2019s Oscar-winning performance and became a cultural phenomenon.\n\n12. **1917 (2019)** - Directed by Sam Mendes, this war film was praised for its innovative single-shot technique and won multiple awards.\n\n13. **Nomadland (2020)** - Directed by Chlo\u00e9 Zhao, this drama about modern-day nomads won the Academy Award for Best Picture and was celebrated for its naturalistic performances and direction.\n\n14. **Dune (2021)** - Directed by Denis Villeneuve, this adaptation of the classic sci-fi novel received acclaim for its visual spectacle and ambitious storytelling.\n\n15. **Everything Everywhere All at Once (2022)** - Directed by Daniel Kwan and Daniel Scheinert, this genre-blending film was praised for its originality, performances, and emotional depth.\n\nThese films represent a mix of genres, styles, and cultural impacts that have resonated with audiences and critics alike over the past twenty years.",
